comments.body: Shouldn't we prioritize spelling fix over import here too ?

A user actually requested that we not do that: https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/23258#issuecomment-379764815

I think this makes sense -- it's more likely that you misspelled some existing property than that you forgot to declare a different property with nearly the same name. But if you have `import { foo1 } from "mod";`, we don't want to correct all `foo2` to `foo1` if `foo2` actually does exist. The difference in the latter case is we actually do know that `foo2` is a valid name, it just wasn't imported; whereas in the property declaration case we have no evidence that there was ever supposed to be a second property.
I generally agree with @krryan's intuition, and I'm okay with experimenting a little bit here. Let's let the import come first.
